    "name": "M-Walk",
    "description": "M-Walk is a graph-walking agent developed to address sparse rewards in knowledge base completion by learning policies for walking over a graph towards a target node. It consists of a deep recurrent neural network (RNN) and Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS). The RNN encodes the state (the history of the walked path) and maps it separately to both a policy and Q-values. To train effectively, M-Walk combines MCTS with the neural policy to generate trajectories yielding more positive rewards. These trajectories are used for off-policy improvement via Q-learning, which modifies the RNN's policy using parameter sharing. The algorithm repeatedly applies this policy-improvement step to learn the model. At test time, MCTS is combined with the neural policy to predict the target node. Experimental results show that M-Walk learns better policies than other RL-based methods (which mainly use policy gradients) and also outperforms traditional KBC baselines.",
    "keywords": [
        "Graph-walking",
        "Knowledge base completion",
        "Reinforcement Learning",
        "M-Walk",
        "Monte Carlo Tree Search",
        "Recurrent Neural Network"
    ],
